https://seelio.com/w/1at6/smail_-the-smart-mailbox 

WHAT is the expoSItion? 
An annual UMSI event where students exhibit projects to potential employers, peers, prospective students, faculty and UM community.

Project Description
SMail is a hardware device that comes with an associated mobile application.  When a mail is placed inside a user's mailbox, the sensors will send a notification to the SMail mobile application indicating new mail.  The goal of SMail is to make the mailbox handling experience more efficient, fun and engaging for users. 

Students
Rushika Deshpade, Rohan Panicker, Yuepei Guo, Hsin Yen Tu

included.description: SMail is a smart mailbox that could send a notification to your phone when you get new mails. After a serious of observations and interviews, we decided to use weight sensor to detect incoming mails. We created a weight sensor based on Arduino board. To make the mail checking process more engaging, we also designed a mobile app which uses the tamagotchi concept to personify your mailbox.
included.title: SMail: Your Smart Mailbox
